x4freetext: Mass yields and kinetic energy of fragments
Mass of fission fragments was calculated
here A- mass-number of fissible nucleus,
EL and EH- kinetic energy measured for light
of fragments at the fission of U-235
by thermal neutrons was used for normalization.
Of compiler. Titles of Figures 1 and 3 are jumbled in
When crossing to the masses of primary fragments
in value MH was introduced the correction on emission
of prompt neutrons by fission fragments.
kinetic energy of fission fragments are equal
here YM- mass-yield of fission fragments
EK- average kinetic energy of fragments
N-  number of the registered fragments
M.M. Misprint in EN units was corrected in
Subent 003. Dates were corrected for 4-digits year.
AKE -> KE was corrected in Subents 010-012,015-016
according to comment of N.Otsuka (NDS IAEA) .
"PART-DET (FF)" was deleted according to a comment of
Code (SEC) was added in SF5 - see CORRECTION (probably
from authors), but no explanation in the article;
